Citation.sTitle: Density and Viscosity of 2-Butanol + (1-Propanol, 2-Propanol, or 3-Amino-1-propanol) Mixtures at Temperatures of (293.15 to 323.15) K: Application of the ERAS Model
Citation.sAbstract: In this work, density, , and viscosity, , of pure components of 1-propanol, 2-propanol, 3-amino-1-propanol, and 2-butanol along with the binary mixtures of {x12-butanol + x21propanol}, {x12-butanol + x22-propanol}, and {12-butanol + 23-amino-1-propanol} were determined over the entire composition range at temperatures (293.15 to 323.15) K. The experimental data of density and viscosity were used to calculate the excess molar volumes, , and viscosity deviations, , of the mixtures. The obtained results show that the values of the mixtures are negative in the whole composition range and increase with increasing temperature. Viscosity deviations of {x12-butanol + x21-propanol} mixture are negative in low temperatures and are positive at high temperatures, while the values of {x12-butanol + x22-propanol} and {12-butanol + 23-amino-1-propanol} mixtures are negative in the whole composition range and decrease with increasing temperature. The excess molar quantities were correlated by Redlich- Kister equation. The ERAS model was used to correlate the excess molar volumes of the mixtures at temperatures (298.15, 303.15, 313.15) K. Comparison between the calculated and experimental values show a good agreement for all three mixtures. Page 2 of 32 Page 3 of 32
